--- A temporary data structure used in the processing of crimes the player has committed.
--- @class tes3crimeEvent
--- @field bountyKey string Contains the stringified version of the type used for bounty-related functions.
--- @field criminal tes3mobileActor|tes3mobileCreature|tes3mobileNPC|tes3mobilePlayer The player mobile will be used as a default value, meaning that there is no direct victim. Other values may be possible but will generally not be reacted to by AI and discarded.
--- 
--- For crimes of type `tes3.crimeType.witnessReaction` the criminal will always be the witness, unless it is reacting to a crime of type `tes3.crimeType.killing`, in which case the criminal mobile will be used.
--- @field position tes3vector3 The position of the crime. This will be the position of the victim of an attack/killing or the position of the criminal otherwise.
--- @field stolenFrom tes3activator|tes3alchemy|tes3apparatus|tes3armor|tes3bodyPart|tes3book|tes3clothing|tes3container|tes3containerInstance|tes3creature|tes3creatureInstance|tes3door|tes3enchantment|tes3ingredient|tes3leveledCreature|tes3leveledItem|tes3light|tes3lockpick|tes3misc|tes3npc|tes3npcInstance|tes3object|tes3probe|tes3reference|tes3repairTool|tes3spell|tes3static|tes3weapon Who was stolen from with this crime. Valid for crimes of type `tes3.crimeType.theft` or `tes3.crimeType.pickpocket`.
--- @field stolenValue number The value associated with the crime. Valid for crimes of type `tes3.crimeType.theft` or `tes3.crimeType.pickpocket`
--- @field timestamp number The time at which the crime has been committed. This is not the time at which the crime has been witnessed.
--- @field type tes3.crimeType The base crime type. Maps to `tes3.crimeType`.
--- @field victim tes3mobileActor|tes3mobileCreature|tes3mobileNPC|tes3mobilePlayer The player mobile will be used as a default value, meaning that there is no victim.
--- 
--- If the default value is set, the proper victim can be retrieved from the stolenFrom field for crimes of type `tes3.crimeType.theft` or `tes3.crimeType.pickpocket`.
--- 
--- For crimes of type `tes3.crimeType.witnessReaction` the victim will always be the player mobile.
--- @field victimFaction tes3faction The faction of the crime victim. This field will always be filled with the correct information, even if player has been set as a default value for the victim.
--- @field witnesses tes3aiPlanner[]? A list of AIPlanners that were able to detect the criminal.
